## Frequently Asked Questions

### Is online counseling as effective as in-person sessions for overthinking?

Yes, online counseling can be just as effective as in-person sessions for managing overthinking. It offers convenient access to mental health care from the comfort of your home. The effectiveness of counseling depends on the therapeutic relationship and your commitment, which can be strong in both formats, depending on your unique needs.

### How long does it usually take to see improvement through counselling?

The timeline for seeing improvement through talk therapy varies based on individual needs and goals. Some people notice positive changes within a few sessions, while others may benefit from longer-term mental health care. The effectiveness of counseling is tied to your active participation and the complexity of the issues being addressed.

